    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what I found and what needs to be done:\n\n### Codebase Findings\n\nAll required utilities already exist — no new packages or helpers needed:\n- `CopyModel(src, dst model.Name)` in `server/images.go` handles manifest copying\n- `manifest.ParseNamedManifest()` / `m.Remove()` / `m.RemoveLayers()` handle deletion (same pattern as `DeleteHandler`)\n- `model.ParseName()`, `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`, and `getExistingName()` handle validation\n- All needed imports are already present in each target file\n\n### Changes (4 files, no new imports)\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `api/types.go` | Add `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` — identical shape to `CopyRequest` |\n| `api/client.go` | Add `Client.Rename()` — POST `/api/rename`, no response body, mirrors `Client.Copy()` |\n| `server/routes.go` | Add `RenameHandler`: validate → 409-check dst → `CopyModel()` → delete src; register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy` |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | Add `RenameHandler` func + `renameCmd` cobra command; register after `copyCmd` |\n\n### Handler Logic Flow\n1. Parse & validate both names (400 if missing/invalid)\n2. Check destination doesn't already exist via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409** if found\n3. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404/500 on failure\n4. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on failure\n5. Return **200** `{\"status\": \"success\"}`",
